Money Stuff =0A A thing that people used to worry about is =E2=80=9Cwhat if=
 index funds get too big=3F=E2=80=9D =0AIf most of the money in the stock m=
arket is not run by people =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/c=
lick=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12384102&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233=
be620525&p=3D01222025>=0A=0A=0A=0AIndex funds and adverse selection=0A=0AA =
thing that people used to worry about is =E2=80=9Cwhat if index funds get t=
oo big=3F=E2=80=9D =0AIf most of the money in the stock market is not run b=
y people who are picking =0Astocks and evaluating companies and deciding ho=
w much they are worth, but by =0Apeople who just buy all the stocks at what=
ever the price is, that seems like it =0Amight have weird results. =E2=80=
=9CWorse than Marxism <>,=E2=80=9D some Sanford C. Bernstein & =0ACo. analy=
sts once called it: With only passive investors, how could the market =0Aal=
locate capital=3F=0A=0AThese days that worry has receded a bit; these days =
